  "iteration": 1,
  "content": "**1. Axiata**\nA fusion of \"axiom\" (fundamental legal principle) and \"data,\" suggesting fundamental intelligence applied to legal analysis. The name is brandable, internationally pronounceable, and scalable beyond contract review into broader legal AI.\n\n**2. Veridex**\nCombining \"veritas\" (Latin for truth) and \"index,\" positioning the company as a truth-finding intelligence system. The name suggests comprehensive analysis and discovery, with strong trademark potential and enterprise appeal.\n\n**3. Cognex Legal**\nBlending \"cognition\" and \"nexus,\" implying intelligent connections and insights. The .legal domain reinforces industry focus while maintaining flexibility for expansion into other legal AI applications.\n\n**4. Luminate AI**\nDerived from \"illuminate,\" suggesting the clarification and insight the platform brings to complex contracts. Clean, modern branding with clear AI positioning and room for growth across legal analytics.\n\n**5. Praxent**\nA portmanteau of \"praxis\" (practice of law) and \"intelligent,\" creating a distinctive invented word. Highly brandable with no descriptive limitations, allowing for unlimited expansion while maintaining legal industry relevance through the classical legal terminology root.\n\nEach name follows successful legal tech naming patterns observed in companies like \nLegalOn, Everlaw\n, and \nIcertis\n, which blend industry relevance with brandable distinctiveness. These names prioritize \nabstract brandability over literal description\n, ensuring \ntrademark protection in today's crowded legal tech market\n while positioning for \nfuture scalability and business evolution\n.",
